<description>
    <short>
        <en>A feature-rich SAML 2.0 Single Sign-On (SSO) plugin for GLPI 11+ with support for multiple Identity Providers, Just-In-Time (JIT) provisioning, and dynamic rule-based permission mapping.</en>
    </short>
    <long>
        <en>Samlsso is a SAML 2.0 Single Sign-On (SSO) plugin designed specifically for GLPI 11+. It connects GLPI with external Identity Providers (IdPs) such as Microsoft Entra ID (Azure), Google Workspace, Okta, and Keycloak.

Key Features:
- Multi-Provider Support: Configure and manage multiple SAML providers simultaneously, allowing different customers or departments to log in to the same GLPI instance using their own IdPs.
- Just-in-Time (JIT) Provisioning: Automatically create new GLPI users on their first successful login.
- Dynamic Rights Assignment: Integrate directly with GLPI's rule engine to assign entities, groups, and profiles based on SAML response attributes.
- Exclusions &amp; Bypasses: Configure rules to bypass SSO for CLI commands, GLPI Agents, local administrators, or specific bypass parameters.
- Security Features: Includes security measures such as SAML response replay validation, certificate modulus matching, and automated session cleanup via GLPI Cron.

If you find an issue or need support, register an issue on GitHub. If you like my work, share me a star of recognition! For everything else, join the Discord community at: https://discord.gg/KyMdkqJcGz.
GitHub: https://github.com/DonutsNL/samlsso</en>
    </long>
</description>
